## AI workflow (the harness)

This repo carries a Claude Code harness ported to **ClickUp** (via the ClickUp MCP). See
`README.md` for the full layer model and setup. The core loop:

- **`/create-ticket`** ÔÇö create a ClickUp task + local work-item spec (`specs/work-items/`)
- **`/ticket-review`** ÔÇö readiness gate (Acceptance Criteria, Edge Cases, Scope required)
- **`/start-ticket`** ÔÇö gate Ôćĺ branch Ôćĺ dispatch `implement` agent Ôćĺ chain `/complete-dev`
- **`/complete-dev`** ÔÇö dispatch `verify` agent; pass Ôćĺ In Review + MR, fail Ôćĺ In Progress
- **`/pr-review`** ÔÇö code review; approve Ôćĺ Dev Done, changes Ôćĺ In Progress
- **`/review-outcome`** ÔÇö QA outcome; pass Ôćĺ Done, fail Ôćĺ QA Reject

All project-management operations route through `.claude/skills/_shared/pm-clickup.md`
(the single ClickUp coupling point). PM config + the status map live in
`.claude/workflow.json`.

### Work-item template

Every work item in `specs/work-items/` follows `specs/work-items/_template.md`, which
requires three sections before AI work begins: **Acceptance Criteria** (Given/When/Then),
**Edge Cases & Error States**, and **Scope** (in/out + dependencies). The `/ticket-review`
gate enforces this.

## Branch and commit conventions

Branch prefixes: `feat/`, `fix/`, `chore/`, `docs/`, `refactor/`
Commits use Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`

**Before committing:** scan staged files for secrets ÔÇö never commit API keys, tokens,
connection strings, or credentials.

### Running git commands

Never prepend `cd <path> &&` to a git command ÔÇö bare `git` auto-discovers the repo. Use
`git -C <path>` if you must target another worktree.

### Working on a pre-existing branch

Before changing anything on a branch that already exists, sync with main first:

```bash
git fetch origin
git merge origin/main
```

